<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-02-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-02-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="1801" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1801">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 823.00/132.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Lima</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-18">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 18, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Following my previous cables on condition here I report that pursuant
                            resolutions adopted by the Junta ex-President Billinghurst was removed
                            from the penitentiary at midnight last night, transferred to Peruvian
                            war vessel, which sailed north with him at four <pb facs="1180" n="1064" xml:id="pg_1064"/> o’clock to-day. Reported he will be released, but
                            not to go south of Peru.</p>
                        <p>The Junta Government highly appreciates Washington’s action, drawing
                            distinction between this and Mexican situation, expressing most cordial
                            sentiments for our country.</p>
                        <p>After a week at the Legation Mrs. Billinghurst and daughters left,
                            renting a house in the city.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">McMillin</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
